content: <articles>    <article xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink/">   <front>     <article-meta>       <title-group>         <article-title>EXPERIENCE OF FREEFEM++ AND NETGEN USAGE  IN THE SIMULATION PROGRAM FOR AERODYNAMIC PROCESSES</article-title>       </title-group>       <contrib-group>         <contrib contrib-type="author">           <name>             <surname/>             <given-names/>           </name>           <aff>             <institution>Doctor of Science in Engineering, professor, Chief Architect of software systems,  Inreco LAN</institution>           </aff>         </contrib>       </contrib-group>       <pub-date pub-type="pub">         <year>2014</year>       </pub-date>       <self-uri xlink:href="http://zenodo.org/record/10139"/>       <self-uri xlink:href="http://zenodo.org/record/10139/files/DubovIR.pdf"/>       <self-uri xlink:href="http://zenodo.org/record/10139/files/DubovIR.png?subformat=icon-90"/>     </article-meta>     <abstract><p>The article describes the experience of using of the open source libraries such as Freefem++ and NetGen to develop a simulation program for aerodynamic processes. Using of these libraries can reduce development time, but it is necessary to solve some technical problems that are described in the article.</p></abstract>   </front>   <article-type>user-innovatika</article-type> </article>   </articles>
